{
  "text": "Szurpiły ( Europe while maintaining small, relict and isolated populations in Scandinavia [CITATION_1] . P. lessonae is a highly warmth-dependent species, requiring water temperatures over 16°C to initiate breeding activity [CITATION_2] . Breeding occurs in late spring and the larval period lasts ca. 2-3 months. The species also suffers from episodes of total breeding failure in high-latitude areas during years with poor climatic conditions (i.e. low temperature; Sj€ ogren 1988).",
